Name: dtumaykin
AboutMe:
From soldering iron in childhood to extreme overclocking in teenage and as a developer now, I have always tried to expand my knowledge (literally burning myself eventually). I am developing commercial applications since 2011, aiming for long term solutions with supreme quality.

I've started by developing application for Microsoft platforms: from ASP.NET web application to Windows Phone and Windows 8 apps (published on Store). Meanwhile, still being in high school, I have developed several projects with Django/Python framework, including a stock exchange simulator. Then I shifted to something more hardcode, developing a C++ video conference software, with bandwidth variability compensation.

In the last few month, I'm dedicated to an Android/iOS application, which allows to perform free calls even without data connection.

Also, #SOreadytohelp.
